Definition: from {{h680}}; noble; Atsel, the name of an Israelite, and of a place in Palestine; Azal, Azel.
from {{h680}} and {{h3050}} prolonged; Jah has reserved; Atsaljah, an Israelite; Azaliah.
a primitive root; properly, to join; used only as a denominative from {{h681}}; to separate; hence, to select, refuse, contract; keep, reserve, straiten, take.
from {{h680}} (in the sense of joining); a side; (as a preposition) near; at, (hard) by, (from) (beside), near (unto), toward, with. See also {{h1018}}.
a primitive root; to store up; (lay up in) store,   (make) treasure(-r).
from {{h686}}; treasure; Etser, an Idumaean; Ezer.
from an unused root probably meaning to be strong; strength (i.e. strong); Otsem, the name of two Israelites; Ozem.
a variation from {{h6807}}; properly, a step-chain; by analogy, a bracelet; bracelet, chain.
from {{h6916}}; burning, i.e. a carbuncle or other fiery gem; carbuncle.
probably from {{h602}}; slender, i.e. the ibex; wild goat.

from {{h599}}; properly, the nose or nostril; hence, the face, and occasionally a person; also (from the rapid breathing in passion) ire; anger(-gry),   before, countenance, face,   forebearing, forehead,   (long-) suffering, nose, nostril, snout, × worthy, wrath.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h637}}; also.

a primitive particle; meaning accession (used as an adverb or conjunction); also or yea; adversatively though; also, + although, and (furthermore, yet), but, even, + how much less (more, rather than), moreover, with, yea.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h6086}}; a tree or wood; timber, wood.
of Persian derivation; Ester, the Jewish heroine; Esther.
of foreign derivation; Esarchaddon, an Assyrian king; Esar-haddon.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h632}} in a legal sense; an interdict; decree.
or אִסָּר; from {{h631}}; an obligation or vow (of abstinence); binding, bond.

a primitive root; to yoke or hitch; by analogy, to fasten in any sense, to join battle; bind, fast, gird, harness, hold, keep, make ready, order, prepare, prison(-er), put in bonds, set in array, tie.
of Persian derivation; Aspatha, a son of Haman; Aspatha.

feminine participle passive of {{h693}} (as if for lurking); a lattice; (by implication) a window, dovecot (because of the pigeon-holes), chimney (with its apertures for smoke), sluice (with openings for water); chimney, window.
feminine of {{h696}} (only in the plural); ambuscades; spoils.
from {{h693}}; ambuscade; den, lie in wait.
from {{h693}}; ambush; Arab, a place in Palestine; Arab.
from {{h7235}}; a locust (from its rapid increase); grasshopper, locust.
the same as {{h695}}; wait.
probably for {{h739}}; a hero (collectively); valiant one.
probably for {{h738}}; lion; Ara, an Israelite; Ara.
a primitive root; to lurk; (lie in) ambush(-ment), lay (lie in) wait.
from {{h691}}; heroic; Areli (or an Arelite, collectively), an Israelite and his descendants; Areli, Arelites.
(Aramaic) plural of {{h607}}; ye; ye.
of uncertain derivation; Asa, the name of a king and of a Levite; Asa.
a primitive root; to shriek; cry, groan.
from {{h602}}; shrieking; crying out, groaning, sighing.
from {{h599}}; an unclean bird, perhaps the parrot (from its irascibility); heron.
(Aramaic) or אֱנַשׁ; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h582}}; a man; man,   whosoever.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h859}}; thou; as for thee, thou.
the same as {{h603}}; some kind of lizard, probably the gecko (from its wail); ferret.
a primitive root; to be frail, feeble, or (figuratively) melancholy; desperate(-ly wicked), incurable, sick, woeful.
from {{h631}}; bound, i.e. a captive; (those which are) bound, prisoner.
or אָסִף; from {{h622}}; gathered, i.e. (abstractly) a gathering in of crops; ingathering.
the same as {{h616}}; prisoner; Assir, the name of two Israelites; Assir.
for {{h615}}; prisoner.
of uncertain derivation; hurt; mischief.
from {{h5480}}; anointed, i.e. an oil-flask; pot.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h612}}; band, imprisonment.
from {{h631}}; a bond (especially manacles of a prisoner); band,   prison.
of uncertain derivation; Asnah, one of the Nethinim; Asnah.
from an unused root meaning to heap together; a storehouse (only in the plural); barn, storehouse.
from {{h659}} (in the sense of hissing); an asp or other venomous serpent; viper.
a primitive root; to surround; compass.
a primitive root; to contain, i.e. (reflex.) abstain; force (oneself), restrain.
or אֲפִיק; from {{h662}} (in the sense of strength); fortress; Aphek (or Aphik), the name of three places in Palestine; Aphek, Aphik.
feminine of {{h663}}; fortress; Aphekah, a place in Palestine; Aphekah.
from an unused root meaning to bestrew; ashes; ashes.
from the same as {{h665}} (in the sense of covering); a turban; ashes.
from {{h6524}} (in the sense of bursting the shell); the brood of a bird; young (one).
probably of Egyptian derivation; a palanquin; chariot.
dual of masculine form of {{h672}}; double fruit; Ephrajim, a son of Joseph; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory; Ephraim, Ephraimites.
patrial from {{h672}}; an Ephrathite or an Ephraimite; Ephraimite, Ephrathite.
or אֶפְרָתָה; from {{h6509}}; fruitfulness; Ephrath, another name for Bethlehem; once (Psalm 132:6) perhaps for Ephraim; also of an Israelitish woman; Ephrath, Ephratah.
(Aramaic) or אֲפַרְסַתְכַי; (Aramaic), of foreign origin (only in the plural); an Apharsekite or Apharsathkite, an unknown Assyrian tribe; Apharsachites, Apharasthchites.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin (only in the plural); an Apherasite or inhabitant of an unknown region of Assyria; Apharsite.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h676}}; finger, toe.
from the same as {{h6648}} (in the sense of grasping); something to sieze with, i.e. a finger; by analogy, a toe; finger, toe.
or אֶצְבֹּן; of uncertain derivation; Etsbon, the name of two Israelites; Ezbon.
(Aramaic) of Persian origin; revenue; others at the last; revenue.
from {{h680}} (in its primary sense of uniting); a joint of the hand (i.e. knuckle); also (according to some) a party-wall (Ezekiel 41:8); (arm) hole, great.
from {{h680}} (in its secondary sense of separation); an extremity (Isaiah 41:9), also a noble; chief man, noble.
from the same as {{h651}} (in the sense of weakness); unripe; not grown up.
dual of {{h639}}; two nostrils; Appajim, an Israelite; Appaim.
rarely אֵפֹד; probably of foreign derivation; a girdle; specifically the ephod or highpriest's shoulder-piece; also generally, an image; ephod.
perhaps from {{h6315}}; breeze; Aphiach, an Israelite; Aphiah.
a primitive root; to cook, especially to bake; bake(-r, (-meats)).
or אֵפוֹא; from {{h6311}}; strictly a demonstrative particle, here; but used of time, now or then; here, now, where?
feminine of {{h646}}; a girding on (of the ephod); hence, generally, a plating (of metal); ephod, ornament.
apparently of foreign derivation; a pavilion or palace-tent; palace.
a primitive root [rather a denominative from {{h646}}]; to gird on (the ephod); bind, gird.
the same as {{h646}} shortened; Ephod, an Israelite; Ephod.
from an unused root probably meaning to breathe; properly, a breath, i.e. nothing; of nought.
from {{h657}} and the plural of {{h1818}}; boundary of blood-drops; Ephes-Dammim, a place in Palestine; Ephes-dammim.
from an unused root meaning to set as the sun; dusky; very dark.
from {{h622}}; properly, containing, i.e. a tube; also a bed or valley of a stream; also a strong thing or a hero; brook, channel, mighty, river,   scale, stream, strong piece.
feminine of {{h651}}; duskiness, figuratively, misfortune; concrete, concealment; dark, darkness, gloominess, × thick.
from the same as {{h651}}; dusk; darkness, obscurity, privily.
from an unused root meaning to revolve; a turn, i.e. a season; fitly.
from {{h6419}}; judge; Ephlal, an Israelite; Ephlal.

from {{h656}}; (sometimes like {{h6466}}); cessation, i.e. an end (especially of the earth); often used adverb, no further; also the ankle (in the dual), as being the extremity of the leg or foot; ankle, but (only), end, howbeit, less than nothing, nevertheless (where), no, none (beside), not (any, -withstanding), thing of nought, save(-ing), there, uttermost part, want, without (cause).
a primitive root; to disappear, i.e. cease; be clean gone (at an end, brought to nought), fail.
plural of {{h699}}; Arubboth, a place in Palestine; Aruboth.
by reduplication from {{h624}}; gathered up together, i.e. a promiscuous assemblage (of people); mixt multitude.
(Aramaic) of Persian derivation; diligently; fast, forthwith, speed(-ily).
passive participle of {{h622}}; collected (only in the plural), i.e. a collection of offerings; threshold, Asuppim.
from {{h622}}; a collection (of fruits); gathering.
from {{h622}}; a collection of people (only adverbial); × together.
feminine of {{h624}}; a collection of (learned) men (only in the plural); assembly.
of foreign derivation; Osnappar, an Assyrian king; Asnapper.
of Egyptian derivation; Asenath, the wife of Joseph; Asenath.

a primitive root; to gather for any purpose; hence, to receive, take away, i.e. remove (destroy, leave behind, put up, restore, etc.); assemble, bring, consume, destroy, felch, gather (in, together, up again), × generally, get (him), lose, put all together, receive, recover (another from leprosy), (be) rereward, × surely, take (away, into, up), × utterly, withdraw.
from {{h622}}; collector; Asaph, the name of three Israelites, and of the family of the first; Asaph.
